Rating: 0
Try adding Dillweed, Lemon Pepper, and Garlic Powder. And more importantly, rather than laying out on paper towels, try baking the crackers on cookie sheet or in baking pan at 250 degrees for 45 minutes. Helps reduce oiliness and enhances taste.

Rating: 3
These are good, but kind of ordinary. I brought them to a Superbowl party, and the guests thought they were out of a box from the supermarket - the last thing you want when you've made something in your own kitchen! I only used 1/4 cup of oil, and I added dill weed and garlic salt. Insted of laying them out on a paper towel overnight, I baked them on a baking sheet for 10 minutes, stirring halfway through, at 250 degrees.

