My mother used to make oyster crackers similar to these. With 2 packets dried ranch dressing, 1 tbs. dill, and 1 tbs. basil. This variation is great, and a nice change from what I'm used to.

Rating: 4
This is a knock off of the Hidden Valley recipe, which is 1 box/16 oz. Oyster crackers, 1/4 cup Vegetable Oil, 1 packet/1 oz. Hidden Valley® Original Ranch® seasoning & salad dressing mix. The last time I made it (which was years ago) it also called for dill and garlic salt. And once all the ingredients were combined, you stirred it every 15 minutes for 1 hour until the crackers had absorbed the ingredients. Either way, these are addictive!!! Kind of like Lays potato chips - you can't eat just one!

