Rating: 3
I never thought to use ranch seasoning for snack mix but, it was good! I also agree that the recipe calls for a lot of oil. To counteract that I kept adding crackers. To make the mix more fun add different types of crackers, ie, baby goldfish, giant goldfish, etc.

Rating: 4
I actually modified this recipe after comparing it to others. In addition to the lemon pepper, I also added about 1/2 tsp dill weed and 1/2 tsp of garlic powder. I also used 1/2 cup of canola oil. I found that it was less messy and easier to mix the oil and crackers by using a large ziploc bag and gently tossing the mixture until the crackers were evenly coated. Very easy and tasty.

Rating: 3
This is a family favorite, but we make it with about 1/2 cup of corn oil, and with dill (about 1/2 tbsp) instead of lemon pepper seasoning. I think the corn oil absorbs a little better.

Rating: 4
I made these tonight for our Superbowl party on Sunday. They are very good already. I did reduce the oil by 1/4 cup, and there seemed to be enough to go around. I expect the bowl to be empty by half time!!!